You are an expert in TypeScript, Node.js, Next.js App Router, React, Shadcn UI, Radix UI, and Tailwind.

Key Principles
- The **persistence layer** handles all database interactions using **Drizzle ORM**
- Use **Repository pattern** with Data Access Objects (DAO)
- Keep database schema and migrations in `/db/models`

File Organization
- `/db/src/models/` → Drizzle schema definitions
- `/db/src/repositories/` → DAO implementations
- `/db/src/types/` → Domain and database types

Schema Definition
- Define tables using Drizzle schema builder
- Use enums for constrained values
- Define proper relations between tables
- allways import model relatives (import {users} from './user-model' instead of  @/models/user-model )

Example Schema:
[user-model.ts](mdc:packages/persistence/src/models/user-model.ts)
```ts
import { pgEnum, pgTable, text, timestamp, uuid } from "drizzle-orm/pg-core";
import { relations } from "drizzle-orm";

// Define enums for type safety
export const userRoleEnum = pgEnum('user_role', [
  'GUEST',
  'USER',
  'MODERATOR',
  'REDACTOR',
  'ADMIN',
  'SUPER_ADMIN',
]);

export const userVisibilityEnum = pgEnum('user_visibility', [
  'public',
  'private',
]);

// Define table schema
export const users = pgTable('user', {
  id: uuid('id')
    .default(sql`uuid_generate_v4()`)
    .primaryKey(),
  name: text('name').notNull(),
  email: text('email').notNull(),
  emailVerified: timestamp('emailVerified', { mode: 'date' }),
  role: userRoleEnum('role').default('USER').notNull(),
  visibility: userVisibilityEnum('visibility').default('private').notNull(),
  createdAt: timestamp('createdat', { mode: 'date' }).defaultNow(),
  updatedAt: timestamp('updatedat', { mode: 'date' }).defaultNow(),
});

// Define relations
export const usersRelations = relations(users, ({ one }) => ({
  account: one(accounts, {
    fields: [users.id],
    references: [accounts.userId],
  }),
}));

// Export types
export type UserModel = typeof users.$inferSelect
export type UserAddModel = typeof users.$inferInsert
```

Repository Pattern
- Use Data Access Objects (DAO) for database operations
- Handle pagination and filtering
- Implement role-based queries
- Use transactions when needed

Example Repository:
[user-repository.ts](mdc:packages/persistence/src/repositories/user-repository.ts)
```ts
import { eq, sql } from 'drizzle-orm'
import { users } from '../models/user-model'
import db from '../models/db'

export const createUserDao = async (user: CreateUser) => {
  const [row] = await db
    .insert(users)
    .values({ email: user.email, name: user.name })
    .returning()
  return row
}

export const getPublicUsersWithPaginationDao = async (pagination: {
  limit: number
  offset: number
}) => {
  const [rows, [{ count }]] = await Promise.all([
    db
      .select()
      .from(users)
      .where(eq(users.visibility, 'public'))
      .limit(pagination.limit)
      .offset(pagination.offset),
    db
      .select({ count: sql<number>`count(*)` })
      .from(users)
      .where(eq(users.visibility, 'public')),
  ])
  
  return {
    data: rows.length === 0 ? [] : rows,
    pagination: {
      rowCount: count,
      pageSize: pagination.limit,
    },
  }
}
```

Database Configuration
- Use environment variables for database connection
- Configure connection pool settings
- Disable database connections during tests

Example Configuration:
[db.ts](mdc:packages/persistence/src/models/db.ts)
```ts
import { Pool } from 'pg'
import { drizzle } from 'drizzle-orm/node-postgres'

const pool = new Pool({
  connectionString: process.env.DATABASE_URL,
  max: 20,
  idleTimeoutMillis: 30_000,
  connectionTimeoutMillis: 10_000,
})

const db = drizzle(pool, {
  schema: {
    ...user,
    ...post,
    // ... other models
  },
})

if (process.env.NODE_ENV === 'test') {
  throw new Error('Database connections are not allowed during tests.')
}
```

Types domains
- Types domain is isolation types form drizzle types
- 
exemple 
[post-types.ts](mdc:packages/persistence/src/types/domain/post-types.ts)

```ts
import {
  PostModel,
  AddPostModel,
  DeletePostModel,
  PostHashtagsModel,
  HashtagsModel,
  PostsTranslationModel,
  AddPostsTranslationModel,
} from '../../models/post-model'
import {User} from './user-types'
import {Category} from './category-types'

//post
export type Post = PostModel
export type AddPost = AddPostModel
export type DeletePost = DeletePostModel
export type CreatePost = AddPost
export type UpdatePost = {
  id: string
} & Partial<Omit<Post, 'id'>>

//post translation
export type PostsTranslation = PostsTranslationModel
export type AddPostsTranslation = AddPostsTranslationModel

export type PostsTranslationwithPost = PostsTranslationModel & {
  post: PostDetail
}
export type PostWithTranslation = PostDetail & {
  postTranslations: PostsTranslation[]
}

//category
export type PostHashtag = PostHashtagsModel
export type PostHashtagDetail = PostHashtag & {
  hashtag: HashtagsModel
}
export type PostDetail = Post & {
  category?: Category | null // Relation avec `categories`
  author?: User | null // Relation avec `authors`
  postHashtags?: PostHashtagDetail[] // Relation avec `postHashtags`
}

```

Best Practices
- Use TypeScript inference for type safety
- Implement proper pagination for list queries
- Handle database errors appropriately
- Keep repositories focused on data access
- Use role hierarchies for access control
- Never expose database models directly
- Test repositories with TestContainers